<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="74" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,151,249]" pageId="13" pageNumber="74">
This genus is widely spread in the Old World (110 species in the Palaearctic, 
<quantity box="[1029,1086,151,177]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.286" pageId="13" pageNumber="74" unit="in" value="90.0">90 in</quantity>
the Afrotropical, and 
<quantity box="[1336,1394,151,177]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7271999999999998" pageId="13" pageNumber="74" unit="in" value="68.0">68 in</quantity>
the Oriental regions (
<bibRefCitation author="Lelej, A. S." box="[347,472,187,213]" pageId="13" pageNumber="74" pagination="82 - 111" refId="ref18138" refString="Lelej, A. S. (2007) Biogeography of mutillid wasps (Hymenoptera, Mutillidae). In: Rasnitsyn, A. P. &amp; Gokhman, V. E. (Eds.), Studies on Hymenopterous Insects. Collection of Scientific Papers. KMK Scientific Press Ltd., Moscow, pp. 82 - 111. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="2007">Lelej 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pagliano, G. &amp; Brothers, D. J. &amp; Cambra, R. &amp; Lelej, A. S. &amp; Lo Cascio, P. &amp; Matteini Palmerini, M. &amp; Scaramozzino, P. L. &amp; Williams, K. A. &amp; Romano, M." box="[484,712,187,213]" pageId="13" pageNumber="74" pagination="5 - 425" refId="ref19407" refString="Pagliano, G., Brothers, D. J., Cambra, R., Lelej, A. S., Lo Cascio, P., Matteini Palmerini, M., Scaramozzino, P. L., Williams, K. A. &amp; Romano, M. (2020 [&quot; 2018 &quot;]) Checklist of names in Mutillidae (Hymenoptera), with illustrations of selected species. Bollettino del Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali di Torino, 36 (1 - 2), 5 - 425." type="journal article" year="2020">
Pagliano 
<emphasis box="[589,638,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="74">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
), ten species of this genus are distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[1207,1334,187,213]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="13" pageNumber="74">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
. Five of them are recorded from this country for the first time.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
